{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a new "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" given a file descriptor. On UNIX systems","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this works for plain files, pipes, and sockets.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"unixNew"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"unix"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fd","kind":"internalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"text":"IOChannelRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib12IOChannelRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The returned "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel"},{"type":"text","text":" has a reference count of 1."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default encoding for "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","isActive":true},{"text":" is UTF-8. If your application","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is reading output from a command using via pipe, you may need to set","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the encoding to the encoding of the current locale (see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_get_charset()"},{"text":") with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_io_channel_set_encoding()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"By default, the fd passed will not be closed when the final reference","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" data structure is dropped."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to read raw binary data without interpretation, then","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"call the ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_io_channel_set_encoding()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function with ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"encoding argument."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is available in GLib on Windows, too, but you should"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"avoid using it on Windows. The domain of file descriptors and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"sockets overlap. There is no way for GLib to know which one you mean","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in case the argument you pass to this function happens to be both a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"valid file descriptor and socket. If that happens a warning is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"issued, and GLib assumes that it is the file descriptor you mean.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelRef"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib12IOChannelRefV7unixNew0D0ACSgSi_tFZ","title":"unixNew(unix:)","roleHeading":"Type Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","